  "text": "Firefox NSS TLS/SSL Implementation Audit - Core Protocol Files\n\nRepository: sg-evals/firefox--871325b8\nBase Directory: security/nss/lib/ssl/\n\nAUDIT FINDINGS:\n\n1. FILE: ssl3con.c (SSL 3.0/TLS Record Processing and Cipher Suite Negotiation)\n   Primary Protocols: SSL 3.0, TLS 1.0, TLS 1.1, TLS 1.2\n   Primary Functions:\n   - ssl3_HandleRecord: Processes incoming TLS records, including decryption, MAC verification, and content type dispatch (line 13721)\n   - ssl3_SendRecord: Implements record-level encryption and transmission for outgoing TLS records (line 2667)\n   - ssl3_NegotiateVersion: Negotiates the protocol version between client and server (line 1313)\n   - ssl3_SetupPendingCipherSpec: Sets up cipher specifications and key material for pending connections (line 1811)\n   Purpose: Core record layer processing for SSL 3.0 and TLS 1.0/1.1/1.2, handles record encryption/decryption, MAC computation, and cipher suite negotiation.\n\n2. FILE: tls13con.c (TLS 1.3 Handshake and Record Processing)\n   Primary Protocol: TLS 1.3 (RFC 8446)\n   Primary Functions:\n   - tls13_HandleClientHello: Processes client hello messages and manages early version negotiation\n   - tls13_HandleServerHello: Processes server hello messages and key share negotiation\n   - tls13_ComputeHandshakeSecrets: Computes handshake traffic secrets using HKDF-Expand-Label (line 1731)\n   - tls13_ComputeApplicationSecrets: Derives application traffic secrets for record protection (line 1804)\n   - tls13_SendKeyUpdate: Implements TLS 1.3 key update mechanism for traffic secret rotation (line 1148)\n   Purpose: Implements the complete TLS 1.3 handshake state machine, secret derivation using HKDF, and 0-RTT handling with post-handshake processing.\n\n3. FILE: dtlscon.c (DTLS-Specific Protocol Handling)\n   Primary Protocols: DTLS 1.0, DTLS 1.2, DTLS 1.3\n   Primary Functions:\n   - dtls_HandleHandshake: Processes fragmented DTLS handshake messages with sequence number tracking (line 274